records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends count 1 to misdemeanor battery-use of dangerous weapon, contrary to Section 940.19(1) and 939.63(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 1.  Convicted.
GUILTY plea entered to the charge in count 2, carry concealed weapon.  Convicted.
On count 1, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
5) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
6) no contact with Damien or Percy Watkins;
7) pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in the amount to be determined by DOC.
On count 2, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for four (4) months, under the Huber Law, commencing on 03-29-16 by 6:00 p.m.
$443.00 court costs imposed.  Cash bail applied.
Court orders cash bail to be applied to court costs on count 2 first and the to count 1.
Minutes.
